{"id":"7746","name":"List Files in Archive","tagline":"Get a list of the files inside your archive (zip, rar, ...) even if they are many subfolders in","icon":"ios13 c946986751 g59653","latest":"23676","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p><img alt=\"iOS 15: Works in iOS 15.1 beta 2, but with an lot of permission dialogs where &quot;Always Allow&quot; doesn't stick\" src=\"https://atnbueno.com/ios15_warn.png\">\n<strong>iOS 15:</strong> Works in iOS 15.1 beta 2, but with an lot of permission dialogs where \"Always Allow\" doesn't stick</p>\n<p>This shortcut generates the list of files inside an archive (zip, rar, ...), including their relative path if they are inside subfolders. The only caveat is that if the archive has a single folder in the first level, this information is lost.</p>\n<p>Depending on the size and the levels of subfolders of the selected archive, the RAM requirements may be significant, but I've processed archives of 250 MB and 700 files without problem.</p>\n<p>The shortcut needs to temporarily save the list to a text file in <strong>iCloud Drive</strong>. It also requires premission to <strong>run shortcuts</strong> because it runs itself (to recursively access all the files in all the subfolders).</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.0.0 - Dec. 11, 2020, 5:54 p.m.</strong></p>"}